**excitation**

data.text/latex:
\begin{verbatim}
excitation(type, t)
\end{verbatim}
Computes different types of excitation signals

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item type : Excitation type

\begin{itemize}
\item[1.  ] \texttt{Triangle}


\item[2.  ] \texttt{Rectangle}


\item[3.  ] \texttt{Hammer}


\item[4.  ] \texttt{SmoothRect}


\item[5.  ] \texttt{SineWave}


\item[6.  ] \texttt{HalfSine}


\item[7.  ] \texttt{HaverSine}


\item[8.  ] \texttt{SweptSine}


\item[9.  ] \texttt{GaussianPulse}


\item[10. ] \texttt{ColoredNoise}

\end{itemize}

\item \texttt{t}: Time vector

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Output}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{F}: Excitation signal

\end{itemize}
